data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual expression tree construction **won't compile** because a new `Func<>` overload takes priority over the `Expression<Func<>>` one. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, etc. — conditional setters are now just regular `if` statements.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two changes here:**

**(a) Same-named properties across sibling complex types** now get a numeric suffix to avoid silent column sharing. If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously mapped to one `Street` column, EF 10 will create `Street` and `Street1`. To preserve shared-column behavior, pin the names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**(b) Nested complex types** now use the full path. `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously column `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

**If you have existing migrations/data**, generate a new migration after upgrading and review it — these column renames will appear as drops + adds unless you pin with `HasColumnName`.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) similarly.
